  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed combinations; a screening sensitivity study is described in the UQ report narrative identifying viscosity and shear-stress exponent as potentially influential, but no structured sensitivity analysis object is linked to this package. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5. Decision: Accepted.",
