      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for velocity and NIH QoIs; GCI < 5% on fine mesh for all operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh refinement study (1.8M, 6.1M, 18.4M cells) performed at baseline operating point (2500 rpm, 5 L/min). GCI for NIH on fine mesh: 3.1%. GCI for area-averaged velocity: 1.8%. All values below 5% threshold. Discretization error budget incorporated into Monte Carlo UQ sampling. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, fluid temperature, hematocrit) documented with measurement uncertainty; replicated in simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump bench test conditions fully documented: inlet velocity profile measured via LDV, fluid temperature 37 ± 0.3 °C, hematocrit 33 ± 1%. All boundary conditions replicated in CFD setup. Measurement uncertainties propagated into Monte Carlo UQ input distributions. Achieved level 4 satisfies MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (MAPE or relative error) defined a priori; comparison includes experimental uncertainty bars; metric evaluated at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH relative error defined a priori as primary comparison metric. Experimental NIH uncertainty ±8% (combined standard uncertainty from repeat measurements). CFD predictions within ±12.1% maximum relative error across all five operating points. Monte Carlo 95th-percentile prediction intervals encompass all experimental values. Achieved level 4 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold; secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distribution, residence time) documented as supporting indicators.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct regulatory QoI for VAD hemolysis submissions per FDA guidance. Wall shear stress and fluid residence time retained as secondary QoIs to support mechanistic interpretation. QoI relevance documented in V&V plan section 2.1. Achieved level 4 satisfies MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under operating conditions spanning the COU envelope; fluid properties match clinical blood analog within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the identical FDA generic pump geometry used in COU. Operating conditions span 2000–3000 rpm and 3–7 L/min, bracketing all five COU operating points. Glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP, density 1056 kg/m³) matches clinical blood within 4%. Achieved level 4 meets MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated to residual tolerance < 1e-5 for all equations; mass imbalance < 0.01% at steady-state solution.",
      "rationale": "All continuity, momentum, and scalar transport residuals converged to < 1e-6. Mass imbalance at pump outlet < 0.004%. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3 for this factor at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent technical review of simulation setup by analyst not involved in original setup; checklist-based review covering mesh, boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, and hemolysis UDF parameters.",
      "rationale": "Independent review conducted by senior CFD analyst using 42-item checklist. Three minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to production runs (impeller rotation direction sign, outlet pressure reference, UDF coefficient units). Final setup approved. Achieved level 3 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison to DNS or high-fidelity LES data for rotating passage flows; hemolysis power-law model coefficients sourced from peer-reviewed calibration study with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published comparison against LES data for centrifugal pump passages (Nicoud & Ducros, 1999; Byskov et al., 2003). Hemolysis power-law coefficients (C=3.62e-5, α=2.416, β=0.785) from Giersiepen et al. calibration; coefficient uncertainty ±10% propagated into Monte Carlo UQ. Model form uncertainty acknowledged in UQ report section 3.2. Achieved level 4 meets MRL 5 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs characterized with probability distributions sourced from measurement data or literature; distributions documented in UQ plan; 5000-sample Monte Carlo propagation performed.",
      "rationale": "Eleven uncertain inputs identified: fluid viscosity, density, hematocrit, inlet velocity profile shape parameter, turbulence intensity, hemolysis coefficient C, exponents α and β, mesh-induced discretization error, rotational speed tolerance, and outlet pressure. Distributions assigned from bench measurements and literature. 5000-sample Latin hypercube Monte Carlo performed. UQ report documents 95th-percentile NIH bounds at all five operating points. A screening sensitivity study described in UQ report section 4.3 qualitatively identifies shear-stress exponent C and viscosity as dominant contributors, but this screening was not formalized as a separate structured sensitivity analysis artifact linked to the package. Achieved level 4 meets requirement.",
      "note": "UQ report narrative references a screening sensitivity study; structured hasSensitivityAnalysis artifact not linked."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Minimum three independent experimental replicates per operating point; inter-replicate variability reported as standard deviation on NIH.",
      "rationale": "Four independent hemolysis test runs performed per operating point using fresh blood analog batches. Inter-replicate NIH standard deviation ≤ 6% at all five operating points. Sample statistics reported in validation dataset. Achieved level 3 satisfies requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, operating conditions, fluid properties) demonstrated equivalent to experimental conditions within measurement uncertainty; any deviations documented with impact assessment.",
      "rationale": "CAD geometry imported directly from FDA benchmark repository (v2.1); dimensional verification confirms pump geometry matches experimental test article within 0.05 mm. Fluid properties matched within 2% of bench measurements. Rotational speed set to measured mean ± 0.3% tolerance. No significant deviations identified. Achieved level 3 meets requirement."
