    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 5 for a Class III VAD device. Monte Carlo UQ performed with 5000 samples across 11 uncertain inputs; 95th-percentile NIH bounds encompass all experimental validation data. Validation MAPE 4.2% for velocity and 12.1% maximum relative error for NIH, both within pre-specified acceptance criteria. Independent technical review completed with all discrepancies resolved. The UQ report narrative describes a screening sensitivity study identifying shear-stress exponent and viscosity as dominant contributors; this information was reviewed by the assessment team and considered sufficient for the current credibility determination. Package accepted for regulatory submission.",
